1
00:00:09,720 --> 00:00:11,480
Mom said you're bringing someone home.

2
00:00:11,759 --> 00:00:13,759
Did you find yourself a
tea maid in the mountains?

3
00:00:14,679 --> 00:00:16,480
I brought back the mountain deity.

4
00:00:17,960 --> 00:00:18,960
Yeah, right.

5
00:00:21,199 --> 00:00:22,199
What does he look like?

6
00:00:22,679 --> 00:00:23,920
You'll see in a bit.

7
00:00:24,399 --> 00:00:25,879
I want to see now.

8
00:00:26,679 --> 00:00:27,679
Dad spoils you,
but I don't.

9
00:00:28,519 --> 00:00:29,519
Don't pull that with me.

10
00:00:29,800 --> 00:00:31,000
Hey, give it back!

11
00:00:31,679 --> 00:00:33,799
Hey, you're a fan too?

12
00:00:34,679 --> 00:00:37,479
I thought you lived in the
mountains, detached from the world?

13
00:00:38,799 --> 00:00:39,799
Put it back.

14
00:00:40,159 --> 00:00:41,880
This pendant is actually pretty nice.

15
00:00:41,920 --> 00:00:42,920
Give me one.

16
00:00:46,079 --> 00:00:47,560
You have good taste.

17
00:00:47,920 --> 00:00:49,079
We have the same bias.

18
00:00:54,799 --> 00:00:56,335
I got stuck in traffic picking up Xiaoxiao.

19
00:00:56,359 --> 00:00:57,479
I'll head over myself.

20
00:00:57,679 --> 00:00:58,920
Don't go out of your way.

21
00:00:59,200 --> 00:01:00,200
Okay.

22
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:10,000
"A Winter Sun Wakes the Wind in Spring Hills' Dream"

23
00:01:13,500 --> 00:01:17,200
(Episode 9: Dripping)

24
00:01:17,480 --> 00:01:19,519
Dad! Comrade Xu, I'm back!

25
00:01:20,359 --> 00:01:23,319
My sweet daughter is back!

26
00:01:26,480 --> 00:01:27,800
You dared to walk in by yourself?

27
00:01:28,159 --> 00:01:29,599
I wanted to wait outside,

28
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:31,078
but your dad came back
and told me to come in.

29
00:01:31,079 --> 00:01:32,079
I couldn't really refuse.

30
00:01:32,120 --> 00:01:33,240
What were you talking about?

31
00:01:35,879 --> 00:01:36,879
Lang Di.

32
00:01:42,760 --> 00:01:43,760
What's going on here?

33
00:01:43,959 --> 00:01:45,000
She's a fan of yours.

34
00:01:45,079 --> 00:01:46,279
Why didn't you say so earlier?

35
00:01:46,319 --> 00:01:47,319
I just found out myself.

36
00:01:54,519 --> 00:01:55,920
Am I seeing things?

37
00:01:56,319 --> 00:01:57,959
Are you really Lang Di?

38
00:01:59,319 --> 00:02:01,119
Yes, it's me. Hello.

39
00:02:01,120 --> 00:02:02,120
Hello, Lu Xiao.

40
00:02:03,879 --> 00:02:05,920
Can I give you a hug?

41
00:02:12,520 --> 00:02:13,360
Three seconds is enough.

42
00:02:13,361 --> 00:02:14,561
Any longer and it'll cost you.

43
00:02:35,960 --> 00:02:36,960
Bro,

44
00:02:38,120 --> 00:02:40,680
the person you brought home is...

45
00:02:47,216 --> 00:02:48,216
[unknown teen girl sound]

46
00:03:25,479 --> 00:03:27,280
Xiaoxiao, come down for dinner.

47
00:03:27,879 --> 00:03:29,080
I'm not eating.

48
00:03:30,080 --> 00:03:32,399
Be good. Your brother
brought a friend home.

49
00:03:32,400 --> 00:03:34,120
Don't be rude. Let's go.

50
00:03:37,319 --> 00:03:39,199
Do you know who that
person he brought home is?

51
00:03:39,319 --> 00:03:41,119
Do you know what his
relationship with him is?

52
00:03:41,120 --> 00:03:42,159
You have no idea.

53
00:03:42,719 --> 00:03:44,400
Just go. Stop talking.

54
00:03:45,120 --> 00:03:46,120
You...

55
00:03:56,680 --> 00:03:57,680
She's not coming.

56
00:03:59,159 --> 00:04:00,599
We can reheat it if she gets hungry.

57
00:04:00,680 --> 00:04:02,080
Let's eat.

58
00:04:04,719 --> 00:04:05,360
Here.
Oh, thank you.

59
00:04:07,400 --> 00:04:09,199
You must have a very busy schedule.

60
00:04:09,599 --> 00:04:12,919
I hear celebrities are always booked solid.

61
00:04:13,319 --> 00:04:14,120
Yes.

62
00:04:14,319 --> 00:04:16,198
I've actually had my agency
turn down a lot of work lately.

63
00:04:16,199 --> 00:04:17,519
I didn't want to overwork myself.

64
00:04:17,759 --> 00:04:19,119
At your level,

65
00:04:19,120 --> 00:04:20,735
there's no need to push yourself so hard.

66
00:04:20,759 --> 00:04:22,559
Taking care of your
health is more important.

67
00:04:23,160 --> 00:04:26,520
The ripe tea Changyang sent me over the
last two years has been great for my health.

68
00:04:27,519 --> 00:04:31,079
You won an international
award two years ago, right?

69
00:04:31,519 --> 00:04:34,479
Yes. That's why I've been a
bit lazy these past two years.

70
00:04:34,480 --> 00:04:36,160
I didn't really want to take on any roles.

71
00:04:36,600 --> 00:04:38,720
It's good to be selective.

72
00:04:39,319 --> 00:04:43,600
When you do act, make
sure it's a masterpiece.

73
00:04:45,336 --> 00:04:47,429
[posting on Weibo that
her OTP is done with]

74
00:04:53,199 --> 00:04:54,279
Goodbye, Uncle and Auntie.

75
00:04:54,959 --> 00:04:55,959
I'll head out now.

76
00:04:56,480 --> 00:04:57,480
I'll walk him out.

77
00:04:58,839 --> 00:05:00,040
This feels surreal.

78
00:05:00,959 --> 00:05:02,199
What did you expect?

79
00:05:03,199 --> 00:05:04,199
Smashing cups and bowls,

80
00:05:04,240 --> 00:05:05,160
and getting kicked out of the house?

81
00:05:05,240 --> 00:05:06,880
That's how it always goes in mini-dramas.

82
00:05:08,360 --> 00:05:09,839
Well, maybe this isn't a mini-drama.

83
00:05:10,560 --> 00:05:12,399
It's a fantasy family arthouse film.

84
00:05:25,839 --> 00:05:26,639
What?

85
00:05:26,800 --> 00:05:28,160
Get in the car.

86
00:06:12,056 --> 00:06:14,843
(I'm done being a fan, it's all fake!)

87
00:06:14,876 --> 00:06:17,150
(All the couples you
all stan are all fake!)

88
00:06:17,430 --> 00:06:20,883
(The Yuhao Qinglang
pairing is totally fake!)

89
00:06:23,836 --> 00:06:25,743
(What proof do you have it's not real?)

90
00:06:26,703 --> 00:06:31,030
(Because Lang Di and
my brother are dating!)

91
00:06:36,569 --> 00:06:39,496
(Who are you fooling with a
picture where you can't see anyone?)

92
00:06:45,856 --> 00:06:47,623
7 Years Ago.

93
00:06:53,879 --> 00:06:56,560
So sweet.

94
00:07:12,296 --> 00:07:15,636
“My brother brought Lang Di home. Are there
really no feelings between you and him?)

95
00:07:30,040 --> 00:07:31,639
Oh, Mr. Zhang.

96
00:07:31,759 --> 00:07:32,976
About the project you mentioned...

97
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:34,799
Yeah, I'm afraid we won't
be able to collaborate.

98
00:07:34,800 --> 00:07:37,000
We'll have to work together next time. Bye.

99
00:07:39,279 --> 00:07:40,279
Where's Lu?

100
00:07:40,959 --> 00:07:43,198
I think he just went to the restroom.

101
00:07:43,199 --> 00:07:44,240
Go on in first.

102
00:07:44,439 --> 00:07:45,360
Once he's back,

103
00:07:45,361 --> 00:07:47,081
you two still need to go over the schedule.

104
00:08:05,199 --> 00:08:06,319
Oh, Lang Di.

105
00:08:06,519 --> 00:08:07,120
I'm so sorry.

106
00:08:07,121 --> 00:08:08,161
I thought you were Han Lu.

107
00:08:13,639 --> 00:08:15,599
Out of nowhere, they handed you this title.

108
00:08:15,600 --> 00:08:17,640
Which executive's heart
did you win over this time?

109
00:08:18,879 --> 00:08:19,879
Don't say that.

110
00:08:20,800 --> 00:08:21,800
Do you remember?

111
00:08:21,801 --> 00:08:23,776
Back then, Sister Lan had
someone read your horoscope.

112
00:08:23,800 --> 00:08:26,239
They said you'd go through
39 romantic trials in this lifetime.

113
00:08:26,240 --> 00:08:27,640
It scared Sister Lan half to death.

114
00:08:28,199 --> 00:08:30,079
She rushed to find a
master to break the curse.

115
00:08:30,240 --> 00:08:31,800
In the end, nine were still left.

116
00:08:32,600 --> 00:08:34,679
Have you counted? Are you there yet?

117
00:08:35,240 --> 00:08:36,600
Do the unrequited ones count?

118
00:08:37,799 --> 00:08:39,679
If unrequited ones count,

119
00:08:39,919 --> 00:08:41,840
then there'd be 13.9 million.

120
00:08:48,799 --> 00:08:51,799
Think about whether you want
to take on this official event.

121
00:08:52,600 --> 00:08:54,279
Attending the event is a small matter.

122
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:57,038
But once you're put on this pedestal,

123
00:08:57,039 --> 00:08:58,919
you'll have to tone down
your self-indulgence.

124
00:08:59,080 --> 00:09:00,399
Am I self-indulgent?

125
00:09:01,919 --> 00:09:03,319
Getting chauffeured around every day...

126
00:09:03,320 --> 00:09:05,440
You'll be exposed in less than a month.

127
00:09:08,840 --> 00:09:10,479
For next week's brand event,

128
00:09:10,480 --> 00:09:11,600
take Lu with you.

129
00:09:11,679 --> 00:09:12,720
I can't make it.

130
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:15,600
Bye.
See you next time.

131
00:09:20,440 --> 00:09:21,440
Hey.

132
00:09:23,200 --> 00:09:24,840
What do you want for dinner? My treat.

133
00:09:25,519 --> 00:09:26,519
No, thanks.

134
00:09:26,879 --> 00:09:27,799
I'm serious.
No need to save me money.

135
00:09:33,519 --> 00:09:35,839
I want the teppanyaki fried rice
from East 10th Street in Lengdian,

136
00:09:35,840 --> 00:09:38,279
the stall that opens
at 7:00 PM every night.

137
00:09:41,519 --> 00:09:42,519
What?

138
00:09:42,600 --> 00:09:43,880
Getting a ride just to eat that?

139
00:09:48,095 --> 00:09:49,095
How boring.

140
00:09:50,120 --> 00:09:51,879
I'm not eating tonight. I'm on a diet.

141
00:09:54,440 --> 00:09:55,800
The license plate can't be traced.

142
00:09:57,279 --> 00:09:58,398
I'm not lying.

143
00:09:58,399 --> 00:09:59,439
It really can't be found.

144
00:09:59,440 --> 00:10:00,798
But I followed it for a while.

145
00:10:00,799 --> 00:10:03,599
This car frequently goes in and
out of a coffee estate in the suburbs.

146
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:09,615
You didn't get a photo
of the person inside?

147
00:10:09,639 --> 00:10:10,639
It's hard to get a shot.

148
00:10:26,159 --> 00:10:27,159
Xiaochun, Xiaochun.

149
00:10:27,559 --> 00:10:28,559
I'm here.

150
00:10:28,799 --> 00:10:30,240
Call the front desk for me.

151
00:10:30,360 --> 00:10:32,759
Sure thing. Connecting to the front desk.

152
00:10:33,360 --> 00:10:34,000
Hello?
Front desk.

153
00:10:35,279 --> 00:10:37,360
Hello, could you connect
me to room service?

154
00:10:37,600 --> 00:10:38,600
Certainly.

155
00:10:51,600 --> 00:10:52,879
Is this room service?

156
00:11:12,360 --> 00:11:14,158
Sir, there's a call for you.

157
00:11:14,159 --> 00:11:15,159
Do you want to take it?

158
00:11:15,559 --> 00:11:16,559
No.

159
00:11:21,279 --> 00:11:22,279
Hello, Xiaoxiao.

160
00:11:23,200 --> 00:11:24,639
Your brother is in the shower.

161
00:11:25,200 --> 00:11:26,759
Is it urgent?

162
00:11:30,066 --> 00:11:31,426
I said not to take it.

163
00:11:34,480 --> 00:11:35,758
When we had dinner at your place last time,

164
00:11:35,759 --> 00:11:38,000
I felt like your sister
was emotionally unstable.

165
00:11:38,600 --> 00:11:40,360
Just now, I told her
you were in the shower,

166
00:11:40,559 --> 00:11:41,960
and she started crying.

167
00:11:42,440 --> 00:11:44,720
Is she having a hard time
accepting you being with a guy?

168
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:47,399
Can you accept it?

169
00:11:52,240 --> 00:11:54,480
I can't accept being with a stalker.

170
00:11:56,159 --> 00:11:57,519
What's wrong with being a stalker?

171
00:12:07,960 --> 00:12:09,799
I meant a stalker fan,

172
00:12:10,279 --> 00:12:11,600
not you.

173
00:12:12,639 --> 00:12:15,600
In fandom, a stalker fan
refers to those extreme ones

174
00:12:15,679 --> 00:12:16,559
who like to follow you around

175
00:12:16,560 --> 00:12:18,480
and disrupt a celebrity's normal life.

176
00:12:19,039 --> 00:12:21,759
They even doxx you to
get IDs and itineraries.

177
00:12:27,080 --> 00:12:29,360
But you actually did
everything I just mentioned.

178
00:12:29,480 --> 00:12:30,639
I didn't falsely accuse you.

179
00:12:31,279 --> 00:12:32,279
So what if I did?

180
00:12:35,080 --> 00:12:36,480
You showed up without warning

181
00:12:36,559 --> 00:12:37,840
and showered in my room.

182
00:12:38,399 --> 00:12:40,600
That's pretty creepy to me.

183
00:12:41,240 --> 00:12:42,799
So what if I did?

184
00:12:45,165 --> 00:12:46,645
It is what it is.

185
00:13:15,080 --> 00:13:16,840
Hey, what's your room number?

186
00:13:17,360 --> 00:13:18,159
Why?

187
00:13:18,360 --> 00:13:19,479
I ordered delivery for you.

188
00:13:19,480 --> 00:13:20,879
I'll have the robot bring it up.

189
00:13:22,159 --> 00:13:24,080
Aren't you filming in Lengdian?

190
00:13:24,480 --> 00:13:26,840
Ordering delivery has nothing
to do with where I'm filming.

191
00:13:29,399 --> 00:13:30,679
I don't eat late-night snacks.

192
00:13:31,480 --> 00:13:32,879
You never eat when you're working.

193
00:13:34,159 --> 00:13:35,240
None of your business.

194
00:13:35,840 --> 00:13:38,000
You have to eat. Hurry up, room number.

195
00:13:39,960 --> 00:13:41,080
Are you really ordering?

196
00:13:41,559 --> 00:13:42,559
It's almost there.

197
00:13:45,240 --> 00:13:48,159
Room 301. Do you even
know what I like to eat?

198
00:13:48,639 --> 00:13:49,798
No fish, no shrimp.

199
00:13:49,799 --> 00:13:50,679
Nothing from the water.
You love carbs,

200
00:13:51,200 --> 00:13:51,799
no cold drinks,

201
00:13:51,800 --> 00:13:54,400
and no sweets because you're
afraid of gaining weight. What else?

202
00:14:24,039 --> 00:14:25,840
Aren't you filming in Lengdian?

203
00:14:26,159 --> 00:14:27,959
East 10th Street in Lengdian,
every night at 7:00 PM,

204
00:14:27,960 --> 00:14:29,640
the teppanyaki fried rice from that stall.

205
00:14:30,159 --> 00:14:31,440
I warmed it up downstairs.

206
00:14:31,559 --> 00:14:33,000
Eat it while it's hot. I'm leaving.

207
00:14:44,330 --> 00:14:49,170
[He's writing where the food is from, and
posting it with Qi Haoyu unable to see it)

208
00:15:02,576 --> 00:15:05,156
(Qi Haoyu is calling)

209
00:15:11,080 --> 00:15:12,239
You blocked my main account.

210
00:15:12,240 --> 00:15:13,440
But you didn't block my alt.

211
00:15:13,639 --> 00:15:14,679
Now, except for Big Qi,

212
00:15:14,759 --> 00:15:16,678
the whole world, including
Little Qi, knows you ate

213
00:15:16,679 --> 00:15:18,798
the teppanyaki fried rice from the stall

214
00:15:18,799 --> 00:15:20,559
that opens at 7:00 PM on East 10th Street.

215
00:15:20,960 --> 00:15:22,158
Don't go straight to sleep after eating.

216
00:15:22,159 --> 00:15:23,199
You'll gain weight easily.

217
00:15:23,679 --> 00:15:24,960
What on earth do you want?

218
00:15:25,879 --> 00:15:27,960
We need to talk in person.

219
00:15:32,159 --> 00:15:33,719
Then come back and make yourself clear.

220
00:15:34,039 --> 00:15:35,559
You're the one asking me to come back.

221
00:15:46,559 --> 00:15:47,840
I want to make up with you.

222
00:15:49,000 --> 00:15:50,159
We were never together.

223
00:15:50,799 --> 00:15:52,240
Then let's start tonight.

224
00:15:57,879 --> 00:15:59,359
I have to start work at 6:00 AM tomorrow.

225
00:15:59,360 --> 00:16:01,159
I really have to go. Goodnight.

226
00:16:17,360 --> 00:16:18,360
I'm in the car.

227
00:16:19,679 --> 00:16:20,840
When are you coming back?

228
00:16:21,440 --> 00:16:22,440
I'm going to Tianyi.

229
00:16:22,480 --> 00:16:23,399
Driver, please drop Han Lu off first.

230
00:16:23,400 --> 00:16:24,735
To handle some business
for my sister's company.

231
00:16:24,759 --> 00:16:26,239
Just drop me off at the
nearest subway station.

232
00:16:26,240 --> 00:16:27,559
It'll take at least two days.

233
00:16:28,440 --> 00:16:29,999
Since it was registered under my name,

234
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:31,000
I have to go.

235
00:16:31,559 --> 00:16:33,599
I'll bring you Tianyi's

236
00:16:33,600 --> 00:16:35,360
best cheese and rose
bagels when I get back.

237
00:16:35,559 --> 00:16:36,559
What on earth?

238
00:16:37,559 --> 00:16:38,480
I have an incoming call.
Talk to you later.

239
00:16:41,559 --> 00:16:43,439
Hey, without me covering for you,

240
00:16:43,440 --> 00:16:44,799
did you two blow your cover?

241
00:16:52,440 --> 00:16:53,440
I need a moment of your time.
Let's meet up.

242
00:16:56,840 --> 00:16:58,480
Can't we just talk over the phone?

243
00:17:00,039 --> 00:17:01,039
It's not convenient.

244
00:17:02,960 --> 00:17:04,599
Come to the office at nine.

245
00:17:06,599 --> 00:17:07,599
Shi Yuhao?

246
00:17:08,599 --> 00:17:11,839
Mr. Know-It-All, you
need to be there. Overtime.

247
00:17:12,599 --> 00:17:13,599
Overtime pay?

248
00:17:22,880 --> 00:17:24,479
Our company will once again request

249
00:17:24,480 --> 00:17:26,480
a joint variety show
appearance from your company.

250
00:17:27,960 --> 00:17:28,960
On what grounds?

251
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:43,240
You secretly took photos of me.

252
00:17:45,039 --> 00:17:46,680
You weren't the one I was photographing.

253
00:17:47,480 --> 00:17:48,279
Who was in that car?

254
00:17:48,280 --> 00:17:49,680
You both know very well, don't you?

255
00:17:51,000 --> 00:17:53,000
This is a video of me taking a cab home.

256
00:17:57,359 --> 00:17:58,359
Wow.

257
00:17:58,759 --> 00:17:59,759
Brother Guo,

258
00:18:00,200 --> 00:18:02,160
you can hail a Mercedes G-Wagon as a cab?

259
00:18:03,440 --> 00:18:04,440
Who would believe that?

260
00:18:05,200 --> 00:18:06,480
Are you trying to bluff me?

261
00:18:07,039 --> 00:18:08,640
Anyway, you don't have any solid proof.

262
00:18:10,599 --> 00:18:11,599
Brother Guo,

263
00:18:12,559 --> 00:18:14,479
you've been in showbiz for so many years.

264
00:18:14,480 --> 00:18:17,400
Do you still think proof
matters more than rumors?

265
00:18:17,759 --> 00:18:19,038
Once the storm of public opinion hits,

266
00:18:19,039 --> 00:18:20,400
the truth is long gone.

267
00:18:22,000 --> 00:18:24,320
Everyone is just looking for
an outlet for their emotions.

268
00:18:29,960 --> 00:18:32,799
I have other photos here.

269
00:18:36,200 --> 00:18:38,359
One video might not prove anything,

270
00:18:39,039 --> 00:18:40,960
but with all this content put together,

271
00:18:41,400 --> 00:18:42,160
and connected,

272
00:18:42,161 --> 00:18:44,759
it's exactly the kind of puzzle
fans love to piece together.

273
00:18:51,759 --> 00:18:52,798
Qinglang, think it over carefully.

274
00:18:52,799 --> 00:18:53,799
I'll give you some time.

275
00:18:57,640 --> 00:18:59,160
I need to use you to make a comeback,

276
00:18:59,359 --> 00:19:01,335
and you're afraid I'll pull
the rug out from under you.

277
00:19:01,359 --> 00:19:03,960
That string of Morse
code is his account, right?

278
00:19:04,599 --> 00:19:06,559
If it's linked to me, we're a couple.

279
00:19:07,400 --> 00:19:08,759
But if it's linked to him...

280
00:19:10,000 --> 00:19:11,000
You know what'll happen.

281
00:19:17,359 --> 00:19:18,598
Who do you think you are?

282
00:19:18,599 --> 00:19:20,599
You've been stripped bare by the public,

283
00:19:20,680 --> 00:19:22,360
yet you're still here stirring up trouble.

284
00:19:29,359 --> 00:19:30,759
What are we having later?

285
00:19:34,000 --> 00:19:36,320
Brother Guo, you should take
a cab back by yourself later.

286
00:19:44,400 --> 00:19:45,400
Wait, what?

287
00:19:53,400 --> 00:19:54,400
Come in.

288
00:19:57,400 --> 00:19:58,400
Uncle.

289
00:20:00,440 --> 00:20:01,440
Have a seat.

290
00:20:26,240 --> 00:20:27,480
You're very smart.

291
00:20:28,359 --> 00:20:29,880
You know exactly where to sit.

292
00:20:32,759 --> 00:20:36,358
This is Changyang's
application for the Hunter School.

293
00:20:36,359 --> 00:20:37,799
I've got it approved for him.

294
00:20:39,160 --> 00:20:42,000
Normally, it takes two years of training

295
00:20:42,359 --> 00:20:43,960
and passing the assessment to get in.

296
00:20:44,839 --> 00:20:46,759
He only needs three
months of intensive training

297
00:20:46,960 --> 00:20:48,680
and to pass the exam.

298
00:20:50,200 --> 00:20:53,000
Changyang has never been
ordinary since he was a kid.

299
00:20:54,160 --> 00:20:57,160
I know him better than you do on this.

300
00:20:59,039 --> 00:21:01,759
When he got into a fight
at school at age twelve,

301
00:21:02,599 --> 00:21:04,839
Lizhen sent him to the mountains.

302
00:21:05,599 --> 00:21:08,400
He struggled to adapt in the first year

303
00:21:09,559 --> 00:21:10,759
and begged to come home.

304
00:21:11,359 --> 00:21:14,200
I told him, "If you want to come home,

305
00:21:14,759 --> 00:21:17,880
come talk to me when you're qualified."

306
00:21:20,240 --> 00:21:25,359
His growth over those eight
years exceeded my expectations.

307
00:21:26,240 --> 00:21:28,160
What shocked me most

308
00:21:29,400 --> 00:21:31,599
was that he let go of his
prejudice against Wenshu.

309
00:21:32,279 --> 00:21:33,279
Through Wenshu,

310
00:21:34,799 --> 00:21:37,279
he even sold his cousin's tea overseas.

311
00:21:38,799 --> 00:21:39,839
When they were kids,

312
00:21:40,680 --> 00:21:44,599
he and Wenshu clashed at every turn.

313
00:21:45,400 --> 00:21:46,680
Whatever Wenshu had,

314
00:21:47,200 --> 00:21:48,279
he wanted to take.

315
00:21:50,160 --> 00:21:52,559
I didn't expect eight
years in the mountains

316
00:21:53,160 --> 00:21:55,359
could change him into who he is today.

317
00:21:56,359 --> 00:21:57,359
So,

318
00:21:58,039 --> 00:21:59,480
regarding the two of you,

319
00:21:59,799 --> 00:22:02,000
I don't want to interfere
or suppress it too much.

320
00:22:02,400 --> 00:22:05,759
I believe he can handle it

321
00:22:06,640 --> 00:22:09,000
and see his choices clearly.

322
00:22:10,599 --> 00:22:11,599
Uncle,

323
00:22:12,160 --> 00:22:14,015
the ambassador title I
received the other day...

324
00:22:14,039 --> 00:22:15,440
Did you help with that?

325
00:22:16,640 --> 00:22:19,319
That wasn't difficult for me.

326
00:22:21,880 --> 00:22:23,640
Then your reason for calling me here today

327
00:22:24,480 --> 00:22:26,519
isn't just to help me
understand Changyang better.

328
00:22:29,640 --> 00:22:31,000
Understanding is the prerequisite.

329
00:22:31,880 --> 00:22:36,240
Respecting his dream is
the best way to support him.

330
00:22:37,880 --> 00:22:39,160
As early as a year ago,

331
00:22:39,440 --> 00:22:40,960
I wanted him to return to the city

332
00:22:41,640 --> 00:22:44,759
to prepare for the college entrance exam,

333
00:22:46,160 --> 00:22:48,519
or study abroad like Wenshu.

334
00:22:49,160 --> 00:22:51,440
He refused back then

335
00:22:52,519 --> 00:22:55,480
and told me he wanted
to go to the Hunter School.

336
00:22:56,440 --> 00:22:57,720
Even without your help,

337
00:22:57,880 --> 00:22:59,279
he could have done it on his own.

338
00:23:00,960 --> 00:23:02,720
If I didn't agree,

339
00:23:04,559 --> 00:23:05,960
he wouldn't have been able to.

340
00:23:07,920 --> 00:23:09,480
The boy is too smart.

341
00:23:10,039 --> 00:23:11,640
By telling me about this,

342
00:23:11,880 --> 00:23:13,480
he was basically telling me

343
00:23:14,960 --> 00:23:16,240
not to stand in his way.

344
00:23:17,119 --> 00:23:18,359
You know him well.

345
00:23:19,319 --> 00:23:20,799
Compared to Wenshu,

346
00:23:21,079 --> 00:23:23,279
I think more highly of Changyang.

347
00:23:24,160 --> 00:23:26,039
Most parents in my position

348
00:23:27,480 --> 00:23:30,119
don't want their children to suffer.

349
00:23:31,720 --> 00:23:33,480
They just want to give them a wealthy life

350
00:23:34,480 --> 00:23:36,759
and carry on the family legacy.

351
00:23:38,920 --> 00:23:42,319
But Changyang changed my mind.

352
00:23:43,720 --> 00:23:45,720
I respect his choice.

353
00:23:47,319 --> 00:23:49,240
I will respect his choice too.

354
00:23:51,640 --> 00:23:53,519
Many things are beyond your control.

355
00:23:54,352 --> 00:23:56,633
Because of your position.

356
00:23:58,039 --> 00:23:59,239
In the face of public opinion,

357
00:23:59,640 --> 00:24:03,480
an individual is like an ant.

358
00:24:05,440 --> 00:24:07,079
You are powerless to change the wind,

359
00:24:07,759 --> 00:24:12,160
and you can't guarantee
there won't be any leaks.

360
00:24:13,599 --> 00:24:15,720
The wind finds every crack,

361
00:24:16,920 --> 00:24:21,279
and a storm is something neither
you nor Changyang can bear.

362
00:24:22,240 --> 00:24:26,480
Nor can I.

363
00:24:46,640 --> 00:24:48,039
Are you on the plane?

364
00:24:48,920 --> 00:24:50,319
I'm not returning until tomorrow.

365
00:24:52,279 --> 00:24:54,880
My bad. I thought you were flying tonight.

366
00:24:55,640 --> 00:24:57,160
It's getting windy here in Shangjing.

367
00:24:57,480 --> 00:24:58,640
A heavy rain is coming.

368
00:24:58,960 --> 00:25:00,279
It's perfectly sunny in Tianyi.

369
00:25:00,759 --> 00:25:01,559
If the heavy rain doesn't stop,

370
00:25:01,560 --> 00:25:02,680
just reschedule your flight.

371
00:25:03,640 --> 00:25:04,880
Don't rush back.

372
00:25:05,640 --> 00:25:07,680
Got it. When I land tomorrow,

373
00:25:07,839 --> 00:25:08,920
will you pick me up?

374
00:25:10,359 --> 00:25:11,359
Yes.

375
00:25:26,039 --> 00:25:27,039
Quick Q&A.
Let's sync up.

376
00:25:29,839 --> 00:25:30,839
Are you not confident?

377
00:25:34,765 --> 00:25:36,325
Banana or cucumber?

378
00:25:36,480 --> 00:25:37,559
You like bananas.

379
00:25:38,480 --> 00:25:39,920
Coffee or tea?

380
00:25:40,039 --> 00:25:41,160
You don't like coffee.

381
00:25:41,759 --> 00:25:43,680
Easy peasy.

382
00:25:47,640 --> 00:25:48,759
Are you looking at me?

383
00:25:53,720 --> 00:25:54,720
Han Lu.

384
00:25:56,880 --> 00:25:58,039
We're starting soon.

385
00:25:58,359 --> 00:25:59,359
Oh, okay.

386
00:26:05,240 --> 00:26:06,439
Time for the quick Q&A.

387
00:26:06,440 --> 00:26:07,440
Banana or cucumber?

388
00:26:07,480 --> 00:26:08,720
- Banana.
- Cucumber.

389
00:26:09,519 --> 00:26:10,639
You like bananas.

390
00:26:10,640 --> 00:26:11,758
That's why I said banana.

391
00:26:11,759 --> 00:26:12,759
I'm on a diet.

392
00:26:13,319 --> 00:26:14,440
Coffee or tea?

393
00:26:14,640 --> 00:26:15,640
- Tea.
- Coffee.

394
00:26:16,759 --> 00:26:17,879
You like tea.

395
00:26:17,880 --> 00:26:19,119
That's why I said tea.

396
00:26:20,920 --> 00:26:21,920
Me too.

397
00:26:24,640 --> 00:26:25,880
Haoyu, iced Americano.

398
00:26:26,240 --> 00:26:27,640
Sister, is there any tea?

399
00:26:28,240 --> 00:26:30,039
We only have hot tea. Is that okay?

400
00:26:30,119 --> 00:26:31,119
I'll try it.

401
00:26:34,559 --> 00:26:35,559
Thanks.

402
00:26:36,319 --> 00:26:37,480
Are there any chopsticks?

403
00:26:37,880 --> 00:26:38,480
Just a moment.

404
00:26:38,481 --> 00:26:40,361
Teacher, let me finish
handing these out first.

405
00:26:43,519 --> 00:26:46,079
Savor it. It's 80,000 a kilo.

406
00:26:46,480 --> 00:26:47,880
Every sip costs thousands.

407
00:26:48,039 --> 00:26:49,319
Don't listen to his nonsense.

408
00:26:51,920 --> 00:26:53,880
Sister, about my next
project with Han Lu...

409
00:26:54,680 --> 00:26:56,119
Is that on my schedule?

410
00:26:56,838 --> 00:26:58,439
Didn't we already shoot the teaser?

411
00:26:58,633 --> 00:26:59,633
The one for Nanlou?

412
00:27:01,680 --> 00:27:04,519
Sister, to be honest,
I really want to do it.

413
00:27:05,039 --> 00:27:06,879
I know the company is under pressure,

414
00:27:06,880 --> 00:27:08,359
but I'll do my best to fight for it.

415
00:27:09,559 --> 00:27:10,960
Let me think about it.

416
00:27:11,240 --> 00:27:13,240
The main issue is convincing the investors.

417
00:27:14,279 --> 00:27:15,679
If you and your company hadn't

418
00:27:15,680 --> 00:27:17,159
tried to dissolve your partnership,

419
00:27:17,160 --> 00:27:18,639
or if Sister Lan were still here

420
00:27:18,640 --> 00:27:19,719
to keep things under control,

421
00:27:19,720 --> 00:27:21,160
the investors wouldn't be an issue.

422
00:27:21,640 --> 00:27:23,279
But right now, the problem is

423
00:27:23,440 --> 00:27:25,920
they don't approve of
pairings outside the company.

424
00:27:27,920 --> 00:27:29,680
The risk is too high, you know?

425
00:27:30,770 --> 00:27:31,770
Understood.

426
00:27:38,359 --> 00:27:39,359
Yeah.

427
00:27:39,480 --> 00:27:40,480
The tea is good.

428
00:27:41,519 --> 00:27:42,720
The coffee is decent too.

429
00:28:44,319 --> 00:28:45,519
What is this?

430
00:28:45,839 --> 00:28:46,880
Two grown men...

431
00:28:46,960 --> 00:28:48,055
Are they out of their minds?

432
00:28:48,079 --> 00:28:49,079
That is disgusting.

433
00:29:52,079 --> 00:29:53,640
President Fang, we have a problem.

434
00:29:53,839 --> 00:29:56,079
Haoyu and Han Lu are trending.

435
00:29:57,119 --> 00:29:58,839
President Fang, how should we handle this?

436
00:29:59,119 --> 00:30:00,639
Should we suppress the search results?

437
00:30:00,920 --> 00:30:02,119
Let's wait until dawn.

438
00:30:03,880 --> 00:30:05,118
You wouldn't let me fly today.

439
00:30:05,119 --> 00:30:06,439
But it didn't rain until tonight.

440
00:30:06,480 --> 00:30:07,319
If I had flown this morning,
I'd be home by now.

441
00:30:08,480 --> 00:30:09,480
Where is home?

442
00:30:10,160 --> 00:30:11,319
Home is in your heart.

443
00:30:14,640 --> 00:30:15,960
Aren't you sweet, little brother?

444
00:30:20,880 --> 00:30:21,880
Changyang.

445
00:30:22,279 --> 00:30:24,079
How badly do you want
to go to Hunter School?

446
00:30:25,960 --> 00:30:26,960
Very badly.

447
00:30:31,279 --> 00:30:32,279
To what extent?

448
00:30:32,759 --> 00:30:33,839
Give me an analogy.

449
00:30:34,759 --> 00:30:37,480
As much as I want to
fly to your side right now.

450
00:30:40,440 --> 00:30:42,359
I won't be able to pick you up tomorrow.

451
00:30:43,480 --> 00:30:44,480
Why not?

452
00:30:47,160 --> 00:30:49,359
I have to attend an
official event in Langcheng.

453
00:30:50,279 --> 00:30:51,759
Then I'll fly straight to Langcheng.

454
00:30:54,119 --> 00:30:55,119
Stop fooling around.

455
00:30:55,920 --> 00:30:57,640
Be good. Wait for me to get back.

456
00:31:00,937 --> 00:31:02,456
Many things are out of your control

457
00:31:02,480 --> 00:31:04,359
because of the position you're in.

458
00:31:04,480 --> 00:31:05,440
In the face of public opinion,

459
00:31:05,480 --> 00:31:06,960
you are powerless to change the tide.

460
00:31:07,160 --> 00:31:10,279
And the storm is something you
and Changyang cannot weather.

461
00:31:22,240 --> 00:31:23,880
Towel. Hand me a towel.

462
00:31:30,720 --> 00:31:32,358
What are you doing? You just showered.

463
00:31:32,359 --> 00:31:33,359
I'm showering again.

464
00:31:47,359 --> 00:31:49,439
President Fang, it's at
60 million and still rising.

465
00:31:49,920 --> 00:31:51,039
Oh, President Fang.

466
00:31:51,119 --> 00:31:53,358
Your company really
knows how to handle fans.

467
00:31:53,359 --> 00:31:54,639
I should have listened to you sooner.

468
00:31:54,640 --> 00:31:56,960
Hitting 20 million in seconds, haha!

469
00:31:57,319 --> 00:31:58,559
About that matter before,

470
00:31:59,079 --> 00:32:00,680
it was my fault. You know how it is.

471
00:32:00,920 --> 00:32:03,319
Haoyu has been pushing
back against me for a long time.

472
00:32:03,440 --> 00:32:05,039
His heart is entirely with you.

473
00:32:05,480 --> 00:32:06,720
If he were getting blacklisted,

474
00:32:06,759 --> 00:32:08,759
Kevin would have kicked the door open.

475
00:32:09,279 --> 00:32:11,479
No way. In this industry,

476
00:32:11,480 --> 00:32:12,879
we've been around long enough to know

477
00:32:12,880 --> 00:32:15,640
who rises and falls is up to fate.

478
00:32:16,319 --> 00:32:20,879
Last time, I was the one who stopped
Haoyu from attending the brand gala.

479
00:32:20,880 --> 00:32:22,559
The kid is innocent.

480
00:32:22,640 --> 00:32:24,920
Now that Haoyu has won the bet,

481
00:32:25,279 --> 00:32:26,519
let's not beat around the bush.

482
00:32:26,640 --> 00:32:28,279
He's in for the next project.

483
00:32:30,519 --> 00:32:32,679
Qi Haoyu signed a betting
agreement with your company?

484
00:32:34,359 --> 00:32:35,440
A safe landing.

485
00:32:38,279 --> 00:32:40,640
Yeah, I'm heading to the manor first.

486
00:32:43,319 --> 00:32:45,559
Okay. Call me when you land.

487
00:33:51,559 --> 00:33:53,159
Where do you think you're following him?

488
00:33:53,480 --> 00:33:54,480
Who are you?

489
00:33:55,079 --> 00:33:56,440
Don't ask what you shouldn't ask.

490
00:33:56,839 --> 00:33:58,359
Don't follow who you shouldn't follow.

491
00:33:58,480 --> 00:33:59,480
Hand over your phone.

492
00:34:14,159 --> 00:34:15,360
This is the last time.

493
00:34:15,679 --> 00:34:16,840
There won't be a next time.

494
00:34:17,400 --> 00:34:18,760
Don't push your luck.

495
00:34:19,559 --> 00:34:21,559
People always ruin
themselves by taking chances.

496
00:34:35,280 --> 00:34:36,840
You didn't mention such a big deal.

497
00:34:37,256 --> 00:34:38,215
It was arranged by the company.

498
00:34:38,239 --> 00:34:39,239
Nothing much to say.

499
00:34:39,296 --> 00:34:39,996
[On the phone with
"Carbon Fibre Little C Hunter"]

500
00:34:40,039 --> 00:34:42,239
Aren't you happy about
the official endorsement?

501
00:34:42,840 --> 00:34:43,840
It's well-deserved.

502
00:34:44,929 --> 00:34:51,476
[Secretary Li sends a picture and indirectly warns
him to stay vigilant against desperate threats.]

503
00:34:51,516 --> 00:34:52,516
Hello?

504
00:34:55,119 --> 00:34:57,079
I still have some things
to handle at the event,

505
00:34:57,519 --> 00:34:58,799
and the reception is pretty bad.

506
00:34:58,840 --> 00:34:59,960
Let's talk when I get back.

507
00:35:08,456 --> 00:35:15,496
[He's looking at Changyang's sister's
crash out comments from earlier]

508
00:35:15,543 --> 00:35:18,643
[The latest tag says "Seems
like Lang Di has a new boyfriend"]

509
00:35:23,719 --> 00:35:25,479
This drama was originally
prepared by Sister Lan

510
00:35:25,480 --> 00:35:27,320
for Lang Di and Shi Yuhao.

511
00:35:27,519 --> 00:35:29,840
Who knew we'd end up playing the roles?

512
00:35:30,119 --> 00:35:32,119
He didn't fight for it
himself, so who's to blame?

513
00:35:33,079 --> 00:35:35,679
I heard he's still trying to get
on a variety show with Lang Di.

514
00:35:37,840 --> 00:35:39,160
Isn't his career completely dead?

515
00:35:40,960 --> 00:35:43,280
No tax evasion, no drugs.

516
00:35:43,840 --> 00:35:45,239
It's not a total career death.

517
00:35:45,840 --> 00:35:46,639
I haven't been paying attention.
Let me see.

518
00:35:48,840 --> 00:35:50,479
Those Weibo posts he
made to play the victim

519
00:35:50,480 --> 00:35:52,160
actually gained him quite a few followers.

520
00:35:52,879 --> 00:35:55,572
[#FromTodayTheSunSetsAtTheSouthTower]

521
00:35:55,659 --> 00:35:58,606
[The name of the series Yuhao
and Qinglang were supposed to film]

522
00:36:02,112 --> 00:36:06,672
[South Tower, see you
at the next point of light!]

523
00:36:36,320 --> 00:36:37,760
Are you with Qinglang?

524
00:36:44,559 --> 00:36:45,719
Have you taken enough photos?

525
00:36:57,960 --> 00:36:58,960
Following us for so long,

526
00:36:59,119 --> 00:37:00,400
did you get anything useful?

527
00:37:01,719 --> 00:37:02,959
Don't waste your breath on him.

528
00:37:06,519 --> 00:37:09,760
Qinglang, I called him
because I wanted to talk to you.

529
00:37:10,079 --> 00:37:11,479
If you don't want to make a scene,

530
00:37:11,480 --> 00:37:13,200
turn off the speakerphone and listen to me.

531
00:37:21,679 --> 00:37:23,480
You must agree to the variety show.

532
00:37:24,159 --> 00:37:25,495
If you want to see the dirt I have,

533
00:37:25,519 --> 00:37:26,519
meet me alone.

534
00:37:37,360 --> 00:37:38,360
Go home.

535
00:37:47,480 --> 00:37:49,079
Mom went to Grandma's.

536
00:38:02,480 --> 00:38:04,360
When the adults are
away, the kids will play.

537
00:38:27,719 --> 00:38:29,199
Don't you have anything to say to me?

538
00:39:29,600 --> 00:39:32,000
The title of Goodwill Ambassador
was given by Old Xu, right?

539
00:39:38,040 --> 00:39:39,040
Changyang.

540
00:39:39,359 --> 00:39:40,640
You are really smart.

541
00:39:41,359 --> 00:39:42,799
So smart it's almost inhuman.

542
00:39:45,839 --> 00:39:47,080
Are you calling me a beast?

543
00:39:47,959 --> 00:39:48,959
A little beast.

544
00:42:03,079 --> 00:42:05,679
What's this? Is there
another brand event tonight?

545
00:42:12,920 --> 00:42:14,400
Are you a tycoon?

546
00:42:23,480 --> 00:42:24,600
Can you even count them all?

547
00:42:29,518 --> 00:42:32,320
You're not scared they're fake?
If so then you're counting for nothing.

548
00:42:37,199 --> 00:42:38,519
1,006 pieces.

549
00:42:41,119 --> 00:42:42,320
How much did this cost?

550
00:42:43,119 --> 00:42:44,159
Over seven million.

551
00:42:45,339 --> 00:42:47,100
Do you have more money than brains?

552
00:42:47,760 --> 00:42:49,079
Gold keeps going up.

553
00:42:49,280 --> 00:42:50,760
It can be liquidated in an emergency.

554
00:42:53,920 --> 00:42:54,920
So tacky.

555
00:42:57,800 --> 00:42:58,800
But practical.

556
00:43:05,280 --> 00:43:06,280
Happy birthday.

557
00:43:07,519 --> 00:43:08,719
Do you still want fan service?
